BeanLocation - Interface in org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.extensible
Interface about package and class path where Bean is located.

When specifying a package path, the .* expression is available, and if the .* expression is attached to the end of the package path,
all Beans are scanned up or excluded to the leaf directory of the child package path that contains the package path.
(The class path does not allow .* expressions.)

If .* expression is not used, import Bean contained in that folder.

inject(Class<?>, Class<R>) - Method in class org.jvault.vault.ClassVault
Method of inject beans into class-type-parameter and return instance of class-type-parameter.
inject(Class<R>) - Method in class org.jvault.vault.ClassVault
Same method as inject(injectTarget, returnType).
inject(Object, Class<R>) - Method in class org.jvault.vault.InstanceVault
Method of inject beans into parameter and return same identified instance of parameter (that may be injected bean).

Unlike ClassVault, InstanceVault does not cache parameters that marked @InternalBean(type = Type.SINGLETON).
This means that the instance returned for each request has the same address value as the instance passed by the user each time.
inject(P, Class<R>) - Method in interface org.jvault.factory.extensible.Vault
Method of injecting beans into parameter.
The package of parameter is included in the package list with access to the vault,
and the injection succeeds only if the accesses paths of bean contains the package of param.
inject(R) - Method in class org.jvault.vault.InstanceVault
Same method as inject(injectTarget, returnType).
